66
00:05:08,548 --> 00:05:09,924
[MIGUEL groans]

67
00:05:11,509 --> 00:05:13,803
The incandescent
flames of love...

68
00:05:13,887 --> 00:05:15,847
burned deep within their hearts.

69
00:05:15,930 --> 00:05:17,140
[MIGUEL laughs]

70
00:05:17,223 --> 00:05:20,060
I see your punches
haven't lost their sting...

71
00:05:20,143 --> 00:05:24,147
And I see your face still
makes an awesome punching bag.

72
00:05:28,276 --> 00:05:30,487
Y'have to admit,
it's quite a coincidence...

73
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:33,740
Who'da thought we'd be
reunited in a town like this?

74
00:05:33,823 --> 00:05:35,241
Sounds like destiny at work.

75
00:05:35,325 --> 00:05:36,743
Sounds like bullcrap.

76
00:05:36,826 --> 00:05:37,911
Oh yeah...?

77
00:05:37,994 --> 00:05:41,122
Then maybe I'm destined
for someone else.

78
00:05:41,206 --> 00:05:43,416
Like perhaps
your friend here.

79
00:05:45,043 --> 00:05:46,920
Just ignore the idiot, Ellis...

80
00:05:47,003 --> 00:05:48,546
Remember what I said.

81
00:05:48,630 --> 00:05:51,091
Never trust a man,
for any reason.

82
00:05:51,174 --> 00:05:52,801
Nadie, you're awful...

83
00:05:52,884 --> 00:05:54,386
That's crazy talk...

84
00:05:54,469 --> 00:05:57,138
Wait, don't tell me you're
still mad about that thing?

85
00:05:57,222 --> 00:05:58,932
[NADIE] What? I don't know
what you're talking about.

86
00:05:59,015 --> 00:06:01,393
Since you seem to have
removed it from your memory...

87
00:06:01,476 --> 00:06:04,020
I'll go ahead and
tell the story...

88
00:06:04,104 --> 00:06:05,939
Our relationship was a...

89
00:06:06,022 --> 00:06:09,484
So Miguel... Are you
asking to get hit again?

90
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:10,985
[MIGUEL whimpers]

91
00:06:18,993 --> 00:06:21,162
How much longer you
gonna be on your break...?

92
00:06:21,246 --> 00:06:23,581
We're expecting
customers any minute.

93
00:06:23,665 --> 00:06:25,583
Not long... I'll hurry.

94
00:06:25,667 --> 00:06:27,794
Don't forget you were
hired out of charity...

95
00:06:27,877 --> 00:06:30,797
Start pulling your weight
around here or you're gone!

96
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:33,133
[acoustic guitar plays]

97
00:06:33,216 --> 00:06:36,094
[YOUNG MIGUEL] Miss Ruiz...
the manager is looking for you.

98
00:06:36,177 --> 00:06:38,680
What the hell
does he want?

99
00:06:42,350 --> 00:06:45,854
Okay, I lied. Manager's
not even here today.

100
00:06:47,981 --> 00:06:49,816
Knowing these people
they're probably making you

101
00:06:49,899 --> 00:06:51,693
do all the crappy jobs, huh?

102
00:06:51,776 --> 00:06:53,778
Go ahead and take
your time eating.

103
00:06:53,862 --> 00:06:55,864
Gracias... Miguel.

104
00:06:55,947 --> 00:07:00,952
♪ Mariachi music ♪

105
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:09,669
[dissonant note]

106
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,926
[YOUNG MIGUEL] You need
a solid instrument

107
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:18,720
to be a good Mariachi...

108
00:07:18,803 --> 00:07:22,807
And my guitar's about
the cheapest you can buy.

109
00:07:22,891 --> 00:07:26,186
Unfortunately, there's only
so much I can do with it.

110
00:07:29,064 --> 00:07:31,066
If there was a way to
get some extra cash...

111
00:07:31,149 --> 00:07:34,444
the first thing I'd do
is go buy a better one.

112
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:42,452
I don't improve...
My ass is fired.

113
00:07:42,535 --> 00:07:43,953
[YOUNG NADIE] Here.

114
00:07:44,037 --> 00:07:45,955
It's not much but
it should help.

115
00:07:46,039 --> 00:07:48,583
That's your week's pay...
I couldn't take that.

116
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:49,709
[YOUNG NADIE] I insist...

117
00:07:49,793 --> 00:07:52,045
Don't worry, I have
more tucked away.

118
00:07:52,128 --> 00:07:55,048
Got nothin' else
to spend it on...

119
00:07:55,131 --> 00:07:56,883
I want to hear you
at your best...!

120
00:07:56,966 --> 00:07:58,134
Okay?

121
00:07:58,218 --> 00:08:00,178
Nadie.

122
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:09,813
I promise I'll
spend it wisely.

123
00:08:13,942 --> 00:08:15,985
[YOUNG MIGUEL] Absolutely
stunning, my dear.

124
00:08:16,069 --> 00:08:18,363
Your beauty shines even
brighter than before.

125
00:08:18,446 --> 00:08:20,156
Are you sure I
can have this...?

126
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,491
Miguel...

127
00:08:21,574 --> 00:08:24,244
I just happened to receive
a windfall yesterday...

128
00:08:24,327 --> 00:08:28,123
And who better to share
my fortune with than you?

129
00:08:35,422 --> 00:08:36,548
Nadie, hey...

130
00:08:36,631 --> 00:08:38,299
You must be heading
back from shopping...

131
00:08:38,383 --> 00:08:40,760
I was hoping you'd be
free later this week...

132
00:08:40,844 --> 00:08:43,430
There are a few things I
wanted to talk to you about.

133
00:08:44,097 --> 00:08:44,806
Uh--

134
00:08:44,889 --> 00:08:46,891
Aahh!

135
00:08:46,975 --> 00:08:48,518
[YOUNG MIGUEL groans]

136
00:08:50,895 --> 00:08:53,523
To hell with men.

137
00:08:54,649 --> 00:08:56,735
[MIGUEL] I feel horrible
about what I did...

138
00:08:56,818 --> 00:08:58,528
I really do.

139
00:08:58,611 --> 00:09:02,824
But I... I've changed,
Nadie. I've matured.

140
00:09:02,907 --> 00:09:06,369
Heck I've even become a
halfway decent Mariachi.

141
00:09:06,453 --> 00:09:07,620
Thanks for paying the bill.

142
00:09:07,704 --> 00:09:10,040
Please let me buy you
dinner and apologize...

143
00:09:10,123 --> 00:09:12,000
I want to pay back
the money you gave me.

144
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:14,252
No, the tacos were
more than enough...

145
00:09:14,336 --> 00:09:16,212
Let's get moving, Ellis.

146
00:09:16,296 --> 00:09:17,464
Yes sir.

147
00:09:17,547 --> 00:09:18,965
Tonight...

148
00:09:19,049 --> 00:09:21,384
I'll be in front of the clock
tower in the town square.

149
00:09:21,468 --> 00:09:23,803
I'll wait as
long as it takes.

150
00:09:51,247 --> 00:09:53,166
[NADIE sighs]

151
00:09:53,249 --> 00:09:55,919
I'm beat...
We should take a nap...

152
00:09:56,002 --> 00:09:57,337
Or sump'm.

153
00:10:00,465 --> 00:10:01,966
Aren't you going?

154
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:03,635
What'd I tell you...?

155
00:10:03,718 --> 00:10:06,221
You can never trust men
where love is involved...

156
00:10:06,304 --> 00:10:08,264
Especially not him.

157
00:10:08,348 --> 00:10:10,642
He says he's an
accomplished mariachi now?

158
00:10:10,725 --> 00:10:12,852
Please, what a crock...

159
00:10:12,936 --> 00:10:15,522
If I run to him like
some lovesick fool...

160
00:10:15,605 --> 00:10:17,732
I'm sure he'll just
end up bamboozlin' me

161
00:10:17,816 --> 00:10:20,402
out of more money anyway.

162
00:10:20,485 --> 00:10:23,655
I am friggin' done with
bein' screwed over by men.

163
00:11:15,331 --> 00:11:19,169
[NADIE] Like he actually
plans to pay me back...

164
00:11:26,468 --> 00:11:30,388
How careless to leave my
darling Ellis all alone.

165
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:45,236
Oh dear...
I can't help myself.

166
00:11:50,992 --> 00:11:52,494
When falling in love...

167
00:11:52,577 --> 00:11:55,747
One tends to lose sight
of everything else.

168
00:11:56,289 --> 00:11:57,999
[L.A. chuckles]

169
00:12:02,087 --> 00:12:03,755
[clock dongs]

170
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:14,474
Guess Nadie's smartened
up a bit, oh well.

171
00:12:18,228 --> 00:12:19,688
Miguel.

172
00:12:23,608 --> 00:12:25,902
Glad you could make it, Nadie.

173
00:12:25,985 --> 00:12:28,113
[gunshot]

174
00:12:29,364 --> 00:12:31,866
[bullet shells clatter]

175
00:12:45,338 --> 00:12:48,133
I can't stay...
My friend is waiting.

176
00:12:48,216 --> 00:12:50,552
If you worried why don't
you give her a call...?

177
00:12:50,635 --> 00:12:52,762
Tell her you'll be
out late tonight.

178
00:12:52,846 --> 00:12:53,930
[NADIE] Quit jerkin' me around

179
00:12:54,014 --> 00:12:55,724
and just give back
the money you owe me.

180
00:12:55,807 --> 00:12:56,766
You know, 'cause of you

181
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:58,935
I was able to become
an honest man...

182
00:12:59,019 --> 00:13:00,729
I could spend the whole
night thanking you

183
00:13:00,812 --> 00:13:02,522
and it wouldn't be enough.

184
00:13:04,065 --> 00:13:07,068
Let us thank the good
Lord for reuniting us.

185
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:14,159
Salud.

186
00:13:18,621 --> 00:13:20,040
[NADIE sighs]

187
00:13:25,754 --> 00:13:27,922
What are you doing?

188
00:13:30,175 --> 00:13:32,552
Idiot...
He's playing you again...

189
00:13:32,635 --> 00:13:34,012
He's a lying liar...

190
00:13:34,095 --> 00:13:36,222
and a rat...
and a cheat.

191
00:13:44,397 --> 00:13:46,858
[NADIE] Is he in
the john or something?

192
00:13:55,992 --> 00:13:57,410
Hey...

193
00:13:57,494 --> 00:13:59,746
either of you happen to see
where my friend got off to?

194
