Sorry, no.

198
00:14:06,086 --> 00:14:08,171
'Scuse me...
Anyone seen my friend...?

199
00:14:08,254 --> 00:14:10,382
He was wearin'
a Mariachi suit...

200
00:14:13,218 --> 00:14:15,053
The man who was
at your table...?

201
00:14:15,136 --> 00:14:17,013
He left earlier by himself.

202
00:14:17,097 --> 00:14:19,099
That dirty snake!

203
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:23,812
Awright, who's got the
crappiest Mariachi band in town?

204
00:14:25,105 --> 00:14:28,983
[MANAGER] Sure, Miguel's been
playing here for a long time.

205
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:30,819
Well, until three days ago.

206
00:14:30,902 --> 00:14:32,153
What was three days ago?

207
00:14:32,237 --> 00:14:33,697
That's when we'd
finally had enough

208
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,615
of his crappy performances...

209
00:14:35,699 --> 00:14:37,909
Loser was chasin'
customers away.

210
00:14:40,036 --> 00:14:43,123
I don't know what your business
with the guy is so forgive me...

211
00:14:43,206 --> 00:14:45,834
but if I can offer
some advice...

212
00:14:45,917 --> 00:14:48,962
Stay away from Miguel.
He's nothin' but trouble.

213
00:14:49,045 --> 00:14:50,922
[BARTENDER] Nothin' but
a smooth talking womanizer.

214
00:14:51,006 --> 00:14:54,009
Yeah, thanks buddy...
Don't need to tell me.

215
00:14:54,092 --> 00:14:57,053
Can't tell you where he is now
but I'm sure it's not far...

216
00:14:57,137 --> 00:14:59,347
Think he was hatching
another scheme.

217
00:14:59,431 --> 00:15:01,099
Thought I overheard
him say somethin' about

218
00:15:01,182 --> 00:15:04,019
his cash cow comin' in...
some old friend in town.

219
00:15:04,102 --> 00:15:06,855
An old friend in town...?

220
00:15:06,938 --> 00:15:08,481
Aw crap.

221
00:15:08,565 --> 00:15:10,692
[knocking]

222
00:15:13,695 --> 00:15:14,863
Who's there?

223
00:15:14,946 --> 00:15:17,157
[MIGUEL] It's Miguel.
We met this afternoon.

224
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:19,534
Nadie asked me to come get you.

225
00:15:19,617 --> 00:15:21,077
Nadie?

226
00:15:22,245 --> 00:15:23,705
That's right.

227
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,344
Here's our stop.

228
00:15:38,845 --> 00:15:39,971
[LIRIO] Heh!

229
00:15:41,181 --> 00:15:42,807
[NADIE] Ellis!

230
00:15:46,436 --> 00:15:48,355
[phone rings]

231
00:15:48,438 --> 00:15:50,648
[DESK CLERK] You mean your
friend with the blond hair?

232
00:15:50,732 --> 00:15:52,442
She left with a man
just a minute ago.

233
00:15:52,525 --> 00:15:53,401
[NADIE] Where'd they go?

234
00:15:53,485 --> 00:15:56,112
Sorry...
They didn't say.

235
00:15:57,197 --> 00:16:01,034
[DESK CLERK] Um... Miss?

236
00:16:01,117 --> 00:16:02,535
Uhh...

237
00:16:24,099 --> 00:16:25,934
Where's Nadie?

238
00:16:27,268 --> 00:16:28,061
Close...

239
00:16:28,144 --> 00:16:30,230
Should be here any minute now.

240
00:16:30,313 --> 00:16:31,648
[approaching footsteps]

241
00:16:31,731 --> 00:16:35,360
Lourdes. It's about
time you showed up.

242
00:16:35,443 --> 00:16:36,403
[BOUNTY HUNTER A] Heh.

243
00:16:36,486 --> 00:16:38,655
Oh it's you guys...
What's going on?

244
00:16:38,738 --> 00:16:41,574
I recall a conversation where
you promised to contact us

245
00:16:41,658 --> 00:16:43,118
as soon as they got to town.

246
00:16:43,201 --> 00:16:45,120
No worries,
I hadn't forgotten...

247
00:16:45,203 --> 00:16:47,455
I was planning to bringing
her right to your hotel,

248
00:16:47,539 --> 00:16:50,208
I just had to take care of
a few other things first.

249
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:52,627
But hey, if you're willing
to give me my cut right now,

250
00:16:52,711 --> 00:16:55,547
I'll hand her over to you,
no questions asked.

251
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:58,341
I just need the money...
How much is my cut?

252
00:16:58,425 --> 00:17:01,803
[BOUNTY HUNTERS laugh]

253
00:17:01,886 --> 00:17:03,680
[MIGUEL] Heh, heh, heh.

254
00:17:03,763 --> 00:17:05,390
[BOUNTY HUNTER B]
We're feelin' generous today.

255
00:17:05,473 --> 00:17:07,183
Why don't we just give
you everything we got?

256
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,019
Yeah, that's cool.

257
00:17:09,102 --> 00:17:11,479
You sure? 'Cause we'd just
be gettin' it right back.

258
00:17:11,563 --> 00:17:12,313
[MIGUEL] Uhh...

259
00:17:12,397 --> 00:17:13,690
[gunshot]

260
00:17:15,358 --> 00:17:17,235
[MIGUEL] Wh-What is this?

261
00:17:17,318 --> 00:17:18,653
[BOUNTY HUNTER A] Apparently
you got trouble keepin'

262
00:17:18,737 --> 00:17:20,030
your hands off the ladies.

263
00:17:20,113 --> 00:17:21,364
[MIGUEL] What?

264
00:17:21,448 --> 00:17:22,032
[BOUNTY HUNTER B] The boss
of a certain little town

265
00:17:22,115 --> 00:17:23,575
is pissed at you...

266
00:17:23,658 --> 00:17:26,119
He's telling everyone 'bout
how you "ruined his daughter."

267
00:17:26,202 --> 00:17:28,204
See...?
He's real pissed.

268
00:17:28,288 --> 00:17:30,123
[BOUNTY HUNTER B] That got sent
to every hotel in the area

269
00:17:30,206 --> 00:17:32,125
just a minute ago.

270
00:17:32,208 --> 00:17:35,045
[BOUNTY HUNTER A] Y'got a pretty
sweet price on your head, boy.

271
00:17:35,128 --> 00:17:37,213
Here we were
waiting for our goose...

272
00:17:37,297 --> 00:17:38,715
when all of a sudden
our golden egg

273
00:17:38,798 --> 00:17:40,508
came rolling in
right at our feet.

274
00:17:40,592 --> 00:17:42,093
Who, that guy again...?!

275
00:17:42,177 --> 00:17:44,637
People always mix us up...
You're not the first...

276
00:17:44,721 --> 00:17:46,848
Come on man,
you gotta believe me.

277
00:17:46,931 --> 00:17:49,476
I'm just a poor
struggling Mariachi...

278
00:17:49,559 --> 00:17:51,478
I'd never even consider
putting my hands

279
00:17:51,561 --> 00:17:52,979
on the daughter of some boss!

280
00:17:53,063 --> 00:17:55,273
"A Mariachi who
talks too much."

281
00:17:55,357 --> 00:17:56,983
Oh yeah, this is you.

282
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:59,402
The guy you're looking
for is a Mariachi too...

283
00:17:59,486 --> 00:18:01,821
I know where he is,
you want I can take you to him.

284
00:18:01,905 --> 00:18:03,031
[BOUNTY HUNTER C]
Says here to watch out

285
00:18:03,114 --> 00:18:04,824
for your silver tongue.

286
00:18:04,908 --> 00:18:07,911
And too bad for you,
also says "dead or alive."

287
00:18:07,994 --> 00:18:09,412
[BOUNTY HUNTER A laughs]

288
00:18:09,496 --> 00:18:12,040
Listen, I've got some
money coming in...

289
00:18:12,123 --> 00:18:13,500
Let's talk...

290
00:18:20,048 --> 00:18:22,175
[BOUNTY HUNTER A groans]

291
00:18:23,927 --> 00:18:26,429
[NADIE] He may be a no good,
womanizing liar...

292
00:18:26,513 --> 00:18:28,640
but he and I still
have some history.

293
00:18:28,723 --> 00:18:30,642
[MIGUEL] Nadie?!

294
00:18:30,725 --> 00:18:32,769
Ellis... Come out.

295
00:18:34,396 --> 00:18:35,730
Okay.

296
00:18:35,814 --> 00:18:37,941
[NADIE] Get back inside,
kill the lights and don't move.

297
00:18:38,024 --> 00:18:39,442
Yes sir.

298
00:18:43,863 --> 00:18:45,865
Awright, you got
two choices here...

299
00:18:45,949 --> 00:18:49,994
Either walk away or fight me...
I'd go with the first one.

300
00:18:51,746 --> 00:18:54,165
Got any last words...
say 'em.

301
00:18:54,249 --> 00:18:56,209
[gunshots]

302
00:18:56,292 --> 00:18:58,545
[MAN D] 'member hearin' about
those bounty hunters in town?

303
00:18:58,628 --> 00:19:00,672
How much you want to bet
that's them shooting?

304
00:19:00,755 --> 00:19:03,174
[MAN E] Geez. This town
is getting too dangerous.

305
00:19:03,258 --> 00:19:04,009
[gunshot]

306
00:19:04,092 --> 00:19:05,343
[LOURDES gasps]

307
00:19:15,228 --> 00:19:17,605
Hey Ellis... Still alive?

308
00:19:18,898 --> 00:19:20,358
Still alive.

309
00:19:21,735 --> 00:19:23,486
Miguel... It's over...

310
00:19:23,570 --> 00:19:26,823
But I got a crap-ton of
questions I gotta ask you...

311
00:19:26,906 --> 00:19:28,450
Come on out.

312
00:19:31,077 --> 00:19:34,414
Miguel... I said,
the coast is clear.

313
00:19:38,752 --> 00:19:40,045
Miguel?

314
00:19:41,796 --> 00:19:43,673
[LOURDES] Ah! Miguel!

315
00:19:44,466 --> 00:19:45,717
[LOURDES] Oh God no!

316
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,344
Miguel, stay with me!

317
00:19:47,427 --> 00:19:49,554
Why did this happen...?

318
00:19:49,637 --> 00:19:52,807
You promised you'd take me
away from this town forever!

319
00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:59,689
[LOURDES sobs]

320
00:19:59,773 --> 00:20:02,192
[NADIE] Ellis... Let's go.

321
00:20:06,321 --> 00:20:07,697
[NADIE] Ellis.

322
00:20:22,796 --> 00:20:24,673
[ROSENBERG] Good morning,
Miss Hayward.

323
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:26,341
Good morning,
Mister Rosenberg.

324
00:20:26,424 --> 00:20:27,884
How are you today?

325
00:20:27,967 --> 00:20:30,470
Could I have a brief
word with you?

326
00:20:30,553 --> 00:20:33,640
I was planning to come speak
with you about this later...

327
00:20:33,723 --> 00:20:35,266
But recently your
reports have been

328
00:20:35,350 --> 00:20:37,102
coming in
consistently late.

329
00:20:37,185 --> 00:20:39,771
Just wanted to make
you aware of it.

330
00:20:39,854 --> 00:20:41,481
Yes, of course...

331
00:20:41,564 --> 00:20:43,983
I'll issue a stern warning
to my underlings...

332
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,985
Good day.

333
00:20:48,655 --> 00:20:51,908
Heh. "Underlings"... nice.

334
00:20:58,373 --> 00:21:00,041
[ROSENBERG chuckles]

335
00:21:02,544 --> 00:21:04,462
[ROSENBERG] Interesting...

336
00:21:04,546 --> 00:21:07,716
Seems a stern
warning is in order.

337
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:32,741
Did it not turn out
just like I said...?

338
00:21:32,824 --> 00:21:36,494
Men are a breed that
simply cannot be trusted.

339
00:21:36,578 --> 00:21:38,538
That's why you never
blindly follow a man

340
00:21:38,621 --> 00:21:40,957
who says he has
feelings for you.

341
00:21:42,042 --> 00:21:44,627
But you followed
after Miguel.

342
00:21:48,006 --> 00:21:50,258
And then that other lady
said she was planning on

343
00:21:50,342 --> 00:21:52,969
going with him too.

344
00:21:53,053 --> 00:21:54,220
That's true...

345
00:21:54,304 --> 00:21:55,847
And you know what...?

346
00:21:55,930 --> 00:21:59,267
I'm sure the list of women he's
deceived over the years is long.

347
00:21:59,351 --> 00:22:00,685
[ELLIS] Was he a bad man?

348
00:22:00,769 --> 00:22:03,271
Yep...
Real bad man.

349
00:22:05,023 --> 00:22:07,692
Thing is...
Even when you know it...

350
00:22:07,776 --> 00:22:10,945
sometimes you just can't
bring yourself to hate 'em.

351
00:22:11,029 --> 00:22:15,367
And that's especially true
between men and women.

352
00:22:17,035 --> 00:22:18,870
So why...?

353
00:22:18,953 --> 00:22:20,830
So why what?

354
00:22:22,665 --> 00:22:24,834
[ELLIS] The incandescent
flames of love.

355
00:22:24,918 --> 00:22:27,504
It doesn't work that way--Eh!

356
00:22:35,512 --> 00:22:37,931
[NADIE tearfully] Stop it,
there's nothing to cry about!

357
00:22:38,014 --> 00:22:40,809
[ELLIS sobs]

358
00:22:40,892 --> 00:22:43,353
[NADIE] What are you
crying for anyway?

359
00:22:43,436 --> 00:22:45,230
[ELLIS tearfully] What?

360
00:22:45,313 --> 00:22:46,690
[NADIE] Forget it...

361
00:22:46,773 --> 00:22:49,275
Just... stop crying.

362
00:22:52,362 --> 00:22:54,239
[ELLIS] Yes sir.

